The paper deals with the problem of learning the structure of Markov networks from data, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The approach presented in the paper, IBMAP, is a probabilistic maximum-a-posteriori approach, which suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also presents an algorithm for structure selection, which involves performing a heuristic local search in the space of possible structures, indicating that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper involves statistical independence tests on data, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves a probabilistic approach, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
